<font color="#FF0000">REPLY TO TOM DIER (ONLY)</font><br>
<tt>Wed Nov  5 20:39:35 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
TOM, you who have been on this site longer than I or any of the newcomers, look at the other two posts between this one and my last: Does that make you proud?  Do you like being referenced to dog poop?  Isn't that a wee bit childish? That's the &quot;style&quot; of your new friends.<br><br>
Recognition? Recognition of what? You have tossed that at me before, and I still don't get it. Recognition of what, being right? Yea, my ego would probably like that, but I really don't need a statue in town center, but, I do feel that all the C.O.'s need to be acknowledged, in combat as medics such as docdel (who I respect the hell out of - incredible guy) or bedpan pushers, we all contributed something. Those that fled to Canada got amnesty, which I was against. Yes, I gave two years of my life, and many more before and after, and I too am Human and would like (like, not need) an official &quot;attaboy&quot; one of these days.  I never wanted it from the very group I tried to save, detested once upon a time, and came to understand as human beings - combat survivors.  This site taught me alot about the other side of the fence.<br><br>
If I &quot;fabricated a lie about laying in front of a train&quot;, and I probably did. I won't go back and look through the archives, to me it was &quot;fire for effect&quot; to make a point, using your term. Jesus man, aren't you holding me up to a &quot;holier then thou&quot; level?  I see lies and contradictions from many others, but that seems to slip by you, why is that?<br><br>
If my tone is self righteous, to you, I can't help it. I am not talking down, or up to you. My friends, esp my wife, are always doggin' me to act and talk more professional, most folks that I know, and the 100's of patients I have had over 25 years of shrinkdome, tell me I talk to them as an equal, not better or one up. That is the goal I have always strived for.<br><br>
Recognition can be good or bad, by the way, being called a &quot;little commie&quot; and a &quot;coward&quot; and other vulgarities by your pack does irk me. Do you allow me that reaction?  How many times have vets flamed over the phrase &quot;baby killer&quot;, yet to me, being called a &quot;draft dodger&quot; is the same slur.<br><br>
Tom, I have watched you change, and join this pack. I have seen and read you a year ago, and learned from you, as well as disagreeing with you. Now you have to reverse the charges, it seems you want the recognition of the likes of Cook and Ed, and are rationalizing your need to lower your standards and fit in.<br><br>
Meanwhile, watch your friends demonstrate their &quot;cleverness&quot; and tell yourself that they are ok.  I don't think you can.
